code_two_sum.content:
```python
def two_sum(nums, target):
    seen = {}
    for j, num in enumerate(nums):
        complement = target - num
        if complement in seen:
            return [seen[complement], j]
        seen[num] = j
```

result: Provided a Python `two_sum(nums, target)` function using a hash map for O(n) lookup, returning indices [i, j] with i < j.

